eed\n!Date when missing/last \nknown encounter\n!Location of disappearance\n!Possible location\n!Captured \u2013 rescued \u2013 captive born\n!Birthdate \u2013 capture/rescue \u2013 release/escape\n!Age if alive\n|-\n|Malivina\n|F\n|100% Russian Traniset\n|2016\n|TINRO\n|TINRO Center \u2013 Dalian Laohutan Ocean Park \u2013 Chimelong Ocean Kingdom \u2013 Linyi Polar Ocean World\n|Captured\n|July 2012 (est.)  \u2013 July 2015 \u2013 Possible escape in 2016\n|8\n|}\n\n== List of deceased captive killer whales ==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n!Name\n!Gender\n!Breed\n!Date of death\n!Cause of death\n!Location of death\n!Captured \u2013 rescued \u2013 captive born\n!Birthdate \u2013 capture/rescue \u2013 release/escape\n!Age at death\n|-\n|Ahab\n|M\n|100% Southern Residents\n|1974\n|Pneumonia\n|U.S. Navy (Hawaii)\n|Captured\n|1960 (est.) \u2013 November 15, 1968\n|14\n|-\n|Ai\n|F\n|100% Icelandic\n|28 August 1995\n|Candidiasis\n|Nanki Shirahama Adventure World\n|Captured\n|1988 (est.) \u2013 October 1989\n|7\n|-\n|Argentinian Capture\n|Unknown\n|100% Argentinian Transiet\n|19? September 1992\n|Capture operations\n|Samborombon Bay Argentina/Transport Truck/Mundo Marino\n|Captured\n|Unknown \u2013 19 September 1992\n|Unknown\n|-\n|Baby Shamu ll\n|F\n|50% Icelandic \u2013 50% Southern Residents\n|16 January 1986<ref>{{cite web|url=http://articles.latimes.com/1986-01-17/local/me-567_1_baby-shamu-ii|title=Baby Shamu II Dies of 'Flu-Like' Viral Disease|date=January 17, 1986|publisher=|via=LA Times}}</ref>\n|Heart Defect/Respiratory Virus\n|Sea World San Diego\n|Captive born\n|5 January 1986\n|11 Days\n|-\n|Belen (Bethlehem)\n|F\n|100% Argentinian\n|4 February 2000\n|Unknown\n|Mundo Marino\n|Captured\n|Unknown \u2013 6 January 1988\n|12+\n|-\n|British Columbia Capture\n|Unknown\n|Unknown\n|September 1962-August 1970\n|Capture operations\n|British Columbia Canada\n|Caputred\n|Unknown \u2013 September 1962-August 1970\n|Unknown\n|-\n|Kalina (Baby Shamu)\n|F\n|50% Icelandic \u