ia|President of the Senate]]|years=1939}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Constantin Argetoianu]]}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{RomanianPrimeMinisters}}\n{{Chairman Senate Romania}}\n{{President Chamber of Deputies Romania}}\n{{RomanianInteriorMinisters}}\n{{Iorga Cabinet}}\n{{First Cristea Cabinet}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Iorga, Nicolae}}\n[[Category:Prime Ministers of Romania]]\n[[Category:Romanian Ministers of Interior]]\n[[Category:Romanian Ministers of Education]]\n[[Category:Romanian Ministers of Culture]]\n[[Category:Members of the Senate of Romania]]\n[[Category:Members of the Chamber of Deputies (Romania)]]\n[[Category:Presidents of the Senate of Romania]]\n[[Category:Presidents of the Chamber of Deputies (Romania)]]\n[[Category:19th-century Romanian historians]]\n[[Category:20th-century Romanian historians]]\n[[Category:Romanian classical scholars]]\n[[Category:Historians of Christianity]]\n[[Category:Romanian historians of religion]]\n[[Category:Economic historians]]\n[[Category:Historians of the Balkans]]\n[[Category:Historians of the Crusades]]\n[[Category:Albanologists]]\n[[Category:Romanian Byzantinists]]\n[[Category:Romanian Latinists]]\n[[Category:Romanian medievalists]]\n[[Category:Military historians]]\n[[Category:Romanian museologists]]\n[[Category:Romanian orientalists]]\n[[Category:Slavists]]\n[[Category:Social historians]]\n[[Category:Urban historians]]\n[[Category:Historians of Romania]]\n[[Category:Historians of World War I]]\n[[Category:Academic journal editors]]\n[[Category:Romanian philosophers]]\n[[Category:Aphorists]]\n[[Category:Philosophers of history]]\n[[Category:Romanian political scientists]]\n[[Category:Political philosophers]]\n[[Category:Former Marxists]]\n[[Category:Romanian Marxists]]\n[[Category:Junimists]]\n[[Category:Romanian anti-communists]]\n[[Category:Conservative Party (Romania, 1880\u20131918) politicians]]\n[[Category:Democratic Nationalist Party (Romania) politicians]]\n[[Category:20th-century Romanian politicians]]\n[[Category:Geopoliticians]]\n[[Category:Pan-European nationalism]]\n[[Category:Leaders of political parties in Romania]]\n[[Category:Romanian anthologists]]\n[[Category:Romanian art critics]]\n[[Category:19th-century biographers]]\n[[Category:20th-century biographers]]\n[[Category:Romanian biographers]]\n[[Category:Male biographers]]\n[[Category:Romanian book publishers (people)]]\n[[Category:Romanian collectors of fairy tales]]\n[[Category:Romanian columnists]]\n[[Category:20th-century Romanian dramatists and playwrights]]\n[[Category:Male dramatists and playwrights]]\n[[Category:19th-century essayists]]\n[[Category:20th-century essayists]]\n[[Category:Romanian essayists]]\n[[Category:Male essayists]]\n[[Category:Romanian ethnographers]]\n[[Category:Romanian fantasy writers]]\n[[Category:Romanian folklorists]]\n[[Category:Romanian magazine founders]]\n[[Category:Romanian literary critics]]\n[[Category:Romanian literary historians]]\n[[Category:Romanian magazine editors]]\n[[Category:Romanian newspaper editors]]\n[[Category:Romanian newspaper founders]]\n[[Category:19th-century Romanian poets]]\n[[Category:20th-century Romanian poets]]\n[[Category:Romanian male poets]]\n[[Category:Romanian radio personalities]]\n[[Category:Romanian translators]]\n[[Category:20th-century translators]]\n[[Category:Romanian writers in French]]\n[[Category:English\u2013Romanian translators]]\n[[Category:German\u2013Romanian translators]]\n[[Category:Greek\u2013Romanian translators]]\n[[Category:Italian\u2013Romanian translators]]\n[[Category:Romanian travel writers]]\n[[Category:Titular members of the Romanian Academy]]\n[[Category:Members of the Polish Academy of Learning]]\n[[Category:Recipients of the Legion of Honour]]\n[[Category:Adev\u0103rul writers]]\n[[Category:People from Boto\u0219ani]]\n[[Category:Eastern Orthodox Christians from Romania]]\n[[Category:Members of the Romanian Orthodox Church]]\n[[Category:Alexandru Ioan Cuza University alumni]]\n[[Category:\u00c9cole pratique des hautes \u00e9tudes alumni]]\n[[Category:Leipzig University alumni]]\n[[Category:Romanian educational theorists]]\n[[Category:Romanian schoolteachers]]\n[[Category:School founders]]\n[[Category:Rectors of the University of Bucharest]]\n[[Category:University of Bucharest faculty]]\n[[Category:Alexandru Ioan Cuza University faculty]]\n[[Category:University of Paris faculty]]\n[[Category:Scouting and Guiding in Romania]]\n[[Category:Scouting pioneers]]\n[[Category:Romanian philanthropists]]\n[[Category:Romanian people of World War I]]\n[[Category:Romanian military personnel of the Second Balkan War]]\n[[Category:Romanian people of World War II]]\n[[Category:Kidnapped Romanian people]]\n[[Category:Deaths by firearm in Romania]]\n[[Category:People assassinated by the Romanian Iron Guard]]\n[[Category:People murdered in Romania]]\n[[Category:Burials at Bellu]]\n[[Category:1871 births]]\n[[Category:1940 deaths]]\n", "name_user": "S.A. Julio", "label": "safe", "comment": "fixing link", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nicolae_Iorga"}
{"title_page": "Jamie Kern Lima", "text_new": "{{BLP sources|date=August 2009}}\n{{Infobox pageant titleholder\n|name=Jamie Kern Lima\n|title=[[Miss Washington USA]] 2000\n|image=Jamie Kern Lima - It Cosmetics Headshot.jpg\n|nationalcompetition=[[Miss USA]] 2000\n|birth_name=Jamie Marie Kern\n|birth_date={{birth date and age|1977|7|16}}\n|birth_place=[[San Rafael, California|San Rafael]], [[California]], U.S.\n|height={{height|ft=5|in=7}}         \n|eye_color=Blue\n|hair_color=Brown\n}}\n\n'''Jamie Marie Kern Lima''' (born July 16, 1977) is an [[Americans|American]] [[Entrepreneurship|entrepreneur]], billion dollar business success story,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/chloesorvino/2017/05/17/jamie-kern-lima-loreal-beauty-it-cosmetics/#4d3446233b4f/|title=How Jamie Kern Lima Built IT Cosmetics Into A $1.2 Billion Business|last=Sorvino|first=Chloe|website=Forbes||language=en|access-date=2017-06-13}}</ref>champion of women, philanthropist, culture-shifter and highly sought-after keynote speaker.\n\n== Biography ==\n\nLima co-founded [https://www.itcosmetics.com/home IT Cosmetics] from her living room and wasn\u2019t able to pay herself for the first three years, while hearing countless Noes from retailers and investors, and working 100+ hour weeks hustling to keep her dream alive. Her passion for her mission, unremitting perseverance, belief and hard word led to her turning every No into an eventual Yes. Jamie grew IT into a top-selling makeup and skincare brand, then sold it to [[L\u2019Or\u00e9al]] for $1.2 Billion cash, in their largest US acquisition to date, making Jamie the first female CEO in L\u2019Or\u00e9al\u2019s 100+ year history. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://wwd.com/business-news/financial/loreal-to-acquire-it-cosmetics-for-1-2b-10495227/|title=L\u2019Or\u00e9al to Acquire IT Cosmetics for $1.2B|last=Collins|first=Allison|website=Women's Wear Daily|language=en|access-date=2016-07-22}}</ref> \n\nJamie is passionate about inspiring and mentoring entrepreneurs, building businesses, making a difference in the lives of women and girls and giving back in a big way. As a passionate speaker, Jamie loves sharing her stories of inspiration, underestimation, overcoming self-doubt, rejection and never giving up. \n\nFrom working as a grocery bagger at Safeway grocery store, <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnbc.com/2018/05/30/jamie-kern-lima-went-from-bagging-groceries-to-building-it-cosmetics.html/|title=This CEO went from bagging groceries to building a billion-dollar cosmetics business\u2014here\u2019s how|last=Hess|first=Abigail|website=CNBC|language=en|access-date=2018-05-30}}</ref> to waitressing at Denny\u2019s, Jamie always hustled to pay her way through school and make her dreams happen. Prior to launching IT Cosmetics, Jamie was an award-winning TV news anchor with beauty challenges including sparse brows and sensitive skin and she could never find products that truly worked.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://abcnews.go.com/Lifestyle/meet-news-anchor-cosmetics-beauty-line/story?id=38336544/|title=Meet the Former News Anchor Who Started a Beauty Line|last=Staff|first=ABC|website=ABC News|language=en|access-date=2016-04-16}}</ref> That\u2019s when IT Cosmetics and Jamie\u2019s mission to empower every woman to believe in her own beauty was born. Jamie\u2019s now shared this vision of inclusivity and inspiration, doing more than 1000 live TV appearances herself on [[QVC]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.entrepreneur.com/article/237379/|title=How a 10-Minute Spot on QVC Turned This Woman Into a $100 Million Cosmetics Mogul|last=Weiss|first=Geoff|website=Entrepreneur|language=en|access-date=2016-11-20}}</ref> where she grew IT Cosmetics to be the largest beauty brand in QVC history. Through her work, Jamie has built an inspired community of millions of women across the country and globally who have shared their stories of overcoming struggle when it comes to confidence and self-worth.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thecut.com/2016/12/it-cosmetics-loreal-jamie-kern-lima.html/|title=The Beauty Queen of QVC Jamie Kern Lima sells confidence for $39.56, brush included.|last=Wells|first=Linda|website=The Cut|language=en|access-date=2016-12-30}}</ref> \n\nJamie graduated Valedictorian from [[Washington State University]]and received her MBA from Columbia University.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www8.gsb.columbia.edu/reunion/jamie-kern-lima|title=Jamie Kern Lima\u201904|last=School|first=Columbia Business|website=Columbia Business School|language=en|access-date=2017-07-21}}</ref>Jamie\u2019s recently been named on the 2019 Forbes Richest Self-Made Women list, <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/profile/jamie-kern-lima/#5fa090f366c1/|title=America\u2019s Richest Self-Made Women|last=Kroll|first=Lisa|website=Forbes|language=en|access-date=2019-06-04}}</ref>Goldman Sachs\u2019 100 Most Intriguing Entrepreneurs, <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gcimagazine.com/marketstrends/segments/cosmetics/IT-Cosmetics-founders-Goldman-Sachs-100-Most-Intriguing-Entrepreneurs-of-2016-398355951.html/|title=IT Cosmetics Founders Honored by Goldman Sachs|last=Doyle|first=Lisa|website=GCI Magazine|language=en|access-date=2016-10-25}}</ref>\nWWD\u2019s 50 Most Powerful Women in Beauty,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://wwd.com/business-news/human-resources/beautys-50-most-powerful-women-8206638/page/3/|title=Beauty\u2019s 50 Most Powerful Women|last=Resources|first=Human|website=Women's Wear Daily|language=en|access-date=2015-02-20}}</ref>\nPorter Magazine\u2019s Incredible Women list and is a member of the CBS Board of Overseers and Harvard Women\u2019s Leadership Forum. She also received the 2019 Columbia University Medal of Excellence,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.happi.com/contents/view_breaking-news/2019-05-23/it-cosmetics-founders-honored-by-columbia-university//|title=IT Cosmetics Founders Honored by Columbia University|last=Staff|first=Happi|website=HAPPI|language=en|access-date=2019-05-23}}</ref>EY Entrepreneurial Winning Women Award,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.beautypackaging.com/contents/view_breaking-news/2013-11-15/it-cosmetics-co-founder-wins-award/|title=IT Cosmetics Co-Founder Wins Award|last=Packaging Staff|first=Beauty|website=Beauty Packaging|language=en|access-date=2013-11-15}}</ref>Columbia Business School\u2019s Distinguished Early Achievement Alumni of the Year Award, Fashion Group International Star Award, the CEW Achiever Award and is the recipient of the 2019 Look Good, Feel Better Dream Ball Award.\n \nJamie is energized by an unremitting passion to inspire and empower girls, women and entrepreneurs and has been featured on [[Good Morning America]], [[Today (American TV program)]],[[CBS This Morning]],[[CNBC]], [[Nightline]], [[Joel Osteen]],[[The New York Times]], [[O,The Oprah Magazine]], [[People (magazine)]], [[Marie Claire]], [[Shape (magazine)]], [[Glamour (magazine)]], [[Cosmopolitan (magazine)]], [[New York Magazine]], [[The Wall Street Journal]] and more. \n \nJamie currently owns part or all of more than 15 companies. She also works passionately with many philanthropic causes including Look Good Feel Better\u00ae, where IT Cosmetics has donated $40 million in product to date to help women face the effects of cancer with more confidence. Jamie lives in [[Southern California]] with her husband Paulo, daughter Wonder and two French Bulldogs Rainbow and Sunshine. \n\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb name|0449463}}\n* [http://www.misswashingtonusa.com Miss Washington USA official website]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20140419043703/http://www.pageant.com/missusa2000/page4.htm Miss USA 2000] - Article at the ''Pageant News Bureau'' discusses Jamie Kern, along with other delegates. Web.archive.org\n\n{{Washington pageant winners}}\n{{Big Brother (U.S. TV series) contestants}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Kern Lima, Jamie}}\n[[Category:1977 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:American television actresses]]\n[[Category:American television reporters and correspondents]]\n[[Category:Big Brother (American TV series) contestants]]\n[[Category:Columbia Business School alumni]]\n[[Category:Miss USA 2000 delegates]]\n[[Category:Businesspeople from Jersey City, New Jersey]]\n[[Category:People from Kennewick, Washington]]\n[[Category:People from the San Francisco Bay Area]]\n[[Category:People from San Rafael, California]]\n[[Category:Washington State University alumni]]\n[[Category:People from Des Moines, Washington]]\n", "text_old": "{{BLP sources|date=August 2009}}\n{{Infobox pageant titleholder\n|name=Jamie Kern Lima\n|title=[[Miss Washington USA]] 2000\n|image=Jamie Kern Lima - It Cosmetics Headshot.jpg\n|nationalcompetition=[[Miss USA]] 2000\n|birth_name=Jamie Marie Kern\n|birth_date={{birth date and age|1977|7|16}}\n|birth_place=[[San Rafael, California|San Rafael]], [[California]], U.S.\n|height={{height|ft=5|in=7}}         \n|eye_color=Blue\n|hair_color=Brown\n}}\n'''Jamie Marie Kern Lima''' (born July 16, 1977) is an [[Americans|American]] [[Entrepreneurship|entrepreneur]] and former [[Journalism|journalist]]. She is the co-founder and CEO of It Cosmetics<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnbc.com/2018/05/30/jamie-kern-lima-went-from-bagging-groceries-to-building-it-cosmetics.html|title=This CEO went from bagging groceries to building a billion-dollar cosmetics business\u2014here's how|last=Hess|first=Abigail|date=2018-05-30|website=CNBC|language=en|access-date=2019-10-02}}</ref> and was also a television news reporter for several years. Prior to that, Lima was a contestant on the [[Big Brother 1 (U.S.)|first season]] of ''[[Big Brother (American TV series)|Big Brother]]''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnbc.com/2018/05/30/jamie-kern-lima-went-from-bagging-groceries-to-building-it-cosmetics.html|title=This CEO went from bagging groceries to building a billion-dollar cosmetics business\u2014here's how|last=Hess|first=Abigail|date=2018-05-30|website=CNBC|language=en|access-date=2019-10-02}}</ref> She had also competed in the [[Miss USA]] pageant and won the Baywatch College Search in 1999, where she appeared on an episode of the television show.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://abcnews.go.com/Lifestyle/meet-news-anchor-cosmetics-beauty-line/story?id=38336544|title=Meet the Former News Anchor Who Started a Beauty Line|website=ABC News|language=en|access-date=2019-10-02}}</ref> Lima credited her experience to first learning about body makeup.\n\n== Biography ==\n\nLima was born Jamie Marie Kern in [[San Rafael, California|San Rafael]], [[California]] but later moved to [[Des Moines, Washington|Des Moines]], [[Washington (state)|Washington]]. She graduated from [[Washington State University]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/chloesorvino/2017/05/17/jamie-kern-lima-loreal-beauty-it-cosmetics/|title=How Jamie Kern Lima Built IT Cosmetics Into A $1.2 Billion Business|last=Sorvino|first=Chloe|website=Forbes|language=en|access-date=2019-10-02}}</ref>\n\nAfter winning the title [[Miss Washington USA]] in late 1999,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/profile/jamie-kern-lima/|title=Jamie Kern Lima|website=Forbes|language=en|access-date=2019-10-02}}</ref> Lima went on to compete in the [[Miss USA]] 2000 pageant held in [[Branson, Missouri|Branson]], [[Missouri]]. The pageant was won by [[Lynnette Cole]] from [[Miss Tennessee USA|Tennessee]].\n\nAlso in 2000, she appeared in [[Big Brother 1 (U.S.)|season one]] of the Reality TV show ''[[Big Brother (American TV series)|Big Brother]]''.<ref name=\"uwire\">{{cite news|url=http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1P1-30177557.html|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110516150856/http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1P1-30177557.html|url-status=dead|archive-date=2011-05-16|title=Washington State U. grad no stranger to attention on 'Big Brother' |date=2000-07-19|accessdate=2007-02-23|publisher=University Wire |first=Susan|last=Swanburg}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1G1-63288214.html|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110516150928/http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1G1-63288214.html|url-status=dead|archive-date=2011-05-16|title=Local Beauty Queen among 'Big Brother' Contestants|publisher=Seattle Post-Intelligencer |date=2000-07-06|accessdate=2007-02-23}}</ref> She was the last female houseguest left on that season. Three men remained after she left.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1G1-65565421.html|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110516150939/http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1G1-65565421.html|url-status=dead|archive-date=2011-05-16|title=Jamie's exit from house leaves all-male finale.|publisher=The Dallas Morning News|date=2000-09-28|first=Michael|last=Mendoza|accessdate=2007-02-23}}</ref>\n\nLima graduated with an MBA from [[Columbia Business School]] in 2004<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www8.gsb.columbia.edu/about-us/board-overseers/jamie-kern-lima|title=Jamie Kern Lima \u201904|last=School|first=Columbia Business|date=2019-03-28|website=Columbia Business School|language=en|access-date=2019-10-02}}</ref> and worked as a field reporter for [[KNDU]] until 2006 when she then moved to [[Portland, Oregon]] where she worked for [[KPTV]]. She remains in contact with the Washington pageant system and hosted the [[Miss Washington USA]] 2006 pageant won by [[Tiffany Doorn]] of [[Woodinville, Washington|Woodinville]].\n\nLima is the co-founder and current CEO of It Cosmetics\u2013a prestige color cosmetics line for face and body. She launched the line in the United States in 2008 and expanded into [[Canada]] in 2009, with its products becoming available in more than 200 beauty boutiques in the United States, as well as being featured on [[QVC]]. It Cosmetics gained a large number of celebrity fans; including many cast members of the hit TV show [[Dancing with the Stars (U.S. TV series)|Dancing With The Stars]], who use both the face and body products. Lima has recently made appearances on the [[Today (U.S. TV program)|TODAY Show]], [[Rachael Ray (TV series)|Rachael Ray]], [[Extra (U.S. TV program)|Extra!]], and [[E! News]] along with many others representing her beauty line. She won the [[Redbook Magazine]] MVP (Most Valuable Product) award for 2008 for her Leg Sculpting Kit, by the name of Smokin' Hot Legs.\n\nLima has also lived in and visited several countries including Thailand, Brazil, Mexico, Australia, Italy, France, Japan and Cambodia. She also did live reports from the [[Vatican City]] for KNDU in [[Kennewick]] on [[Pope John Paul II]]'s death.{{Citation needed|date=August 2009}} In August 2019, Lima announced she would be leaving her role as CEO of IT Cosmetics.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/chloesorvino/2019/08/29/loreals-only-female-ceo-the-founder-of-it-cosmetics-is-leaving/|title=L\u2019Oreal\u2019s Only Female CEO, The Founder Of IT Cosmetics, Is Leaving|last=Sorvino|first=Chloe|website=Forbes|language=en|access-date=2019-08-30}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb name|0449463}}\n* [http://www.misswashingtonusa.com Miss Washington USA official website]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20140419043703/http://www.pageant.com/missusa2000/page4.htm Miss USA 2000] - Article at the ''Pageant News Bureau'' discusses Jamie Kern, along with other delegates. Web.archive.org\n\n{{Washington pageant winners}}\n{{Big Brother (U.S. TV series) contestants}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Kern Lima, Jamie}}\n[[Category:1977 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:American television actresses]]\n[[Category:American television reporters and correspondents]]\n[[Category:Big Brother (American TV series) contestants]]\n[[Category:Columbia Business School alumni]]\n[[Category:Miss USA 2000 delegates]]\n[[Category:Businesspeople from Jersey City, New Jersey]]\n[[Category:People from Kennewick, Washington]]\n[[Category:People from the San Francisco Bay Area]]\n[[Category:People from San Rafael, Cal